children.name: SimulScanEngApp.txt
children.commit_data:
commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

Date:   Mon Jun 23 16:51:08 2014 -0400

    Image Kit update (v6.1)
    
    1.Enabled to generate bounding box for MicroPDF, Maxicode, Aztec. Combined with QR, MiroQR, DataMatrix, PDF which are already supported, the current ImageKit is able to generate bounding box for all 2D barcodes except Han Xin.
    
    Image Kit update (v6.0)
    
    1. New architecture to handle high-res 2D barcodes in SimulScan.
       Please refer to doc"SimulScan_2D_Barcode.doc" on compass: http://compass.mot-solutions.com/doc/485034614/SimulScan_2D_barcode.doc
    2. Change Macro N_THRESH_NEIGHBORS in MATCODES.C to 9 to improve QR decoding performance
    3. Default length of a decodable Korean 3Of5 string is changed to 6.
    
    DCS clearcase label: IMGKIT_6.01D13_DPX08
    libADCOcr.a: version 1.4.8
    
    SimulScanEngine: Architectural changes to support new Image Kit
    
    -Identification and processing is now in one session
    -Changed method names for testing frames on Image Kit
    -Fixed timing issue for Image Kit where token reset was being sent in the middle of addFrame(...)
    -Fixed library, threading for deinitializing UI
    -Updated templates

commit 663b8149eb4c8c23143974459ada1359401c50eb
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 10 10:50:54 2014 -0400

    Default template optimizations
    
    -SimulScanEngine no longer checks for default template when deciding whether or not to show confirmation screen
    -Added ui_result_confirmation parameter on default template and set to "false" to disable confirmation screen
    -Added auto_capture_sensitivity parameter on most default templates and set to more optimal values
    -Removed Passport.xml template (replaced by TravelDoc.xml)
    -Base64 encoded BankCheck.xml, BookNumber.xml, and TravelDoc.xml

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

    1.Enabled to generate bounding box for MicroPDF, Maxicode, Aztec. Combined with QR, MiroQR, DataMatrix, PDF which are already supported, the current ImageKit is able to generate bounding box for all 2D barcodes except Han Xin.
    
    Image Kit update (v6.0)
    
    1. New architecture to handle high-res 2D barcodes in SimulScan.
       Please refer to doc"SimulScan_2D_Barcode.doc" on compass: http://compass.mot-solutions.com/doc/485034614/SimulScan_2D_barcode.doc
    2. Change Macro N_THRESH_NEIGHBORS in MATCODES.C to 9 to improve QR decoding performance
    3. Default length of a decodable Korean 3Of5 string is changed to 6.
    
    DCS clearcase label: IMGKIT_6.01D13_DPX08
    libADCOcr.a: version 1.4.8
    
    SimulScanEngine: Architectural changes to support new Image Kit
    
    -Identification and processing is now in one session
    -Changed method names for testing frames on Image Kit
    -Fixed timing issue for Image Kit where token reset was being sent in the middle of addFrame(...)
    -Fixed library, threading for deinitializing UI
    -Updated templates

    MC-112228 - Missmatch between Simulscan viewfinder & zoom icon when simulscan is closed zoomed in.
    
    When the zoom bar was created, current value was always set to 0, instead current zoom value of the camera. Implemented API's inside ColorCamera.java to set/get the current value of camera zoom and used those while creating zoom bar in the view.

    SimulScanEngine: Major restructuring of SimulScanEngine, to improve state handling and synchronization. Fixes multiple issues, but needs regression testing.
    
    EMBPD00182699 - Simulscan not responds  when simulscan scanner is opened and selecting home button

commit 36e55bb3ea25f9043545f0a30ccaf1f49f35b257
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Mon May 23 14:19:44 2016 -0500

    Fix SS-195/SS-196 - When device starts capturing Postal Image initially Shutter sound can be heard and then during processing of the image the Beep sound can be heard
    
    This is a timing issue. Currently the way we disable shutter sound if by muting audio. We mute audio just before calling takePicture and un-mute right after that. Since mute and un-mute go through other sub-systems there can be delay. The right solution would be to call enableShutterSound(false) when we open camera for simulscan and enableShutterSound(true) when we close the camera.
    
    BSP has to allow us to enable/disable shutter sound. This can be checked using CameraInfo.canDisableShutterSound value. Added SimulScanEngine changes to support this feature. Currently our BSP does not allow for this. We need to create a bug-report on BSP.
    
    Change-Id: I50d6ec480048f7a0411d9056d3798d7973b4917b

commit 60a22cd127b3e92f2a62561397d4bf118895e60f
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 7 11:55:51 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-124327 ANR observed on Multi line template - Category: Flash On/Off Stress
    
    Fix MC-124584 ANR was observed & application did not launch View finder while capturing Unstructured templates
    
    1. Synchronizing on mClosingSyncObject for entire duration of free-form processing, was holding up ImagingThread suspended, when next frame became available and handlePreviewFrame was called. Added additional boolean mbInOCR which indicates a frame is currently being processed.  handlePreviewFrame returns immediately if a frame is being processed.
    2. In case of Multi-Line Form, found an ANR in a situation where Freeform processing thread was busy processing a frame while user already touched the screen to start processing. Since Freeform processing thread and imaging thread are of same priority, freeform processing thread starved imaging thread and this would cause processing timeout and caused an ANR. Added functions in SimulScanPlugin to start/stop processing and also added checks though-out processing code to check for stopped condition. Chose this option instead of killing the freeform thread.
    
    Change-Id: I58d3007b79be135cf282892c79219fcce3bf125b

Date:   Thu Apr 7 11:55:51 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-124327 ANR observed on Multi line template - Category: Flash On/Off Stress
    
    Fix MC-124584 ANR was observed & application did not launch View finder while capturing Unstructured templates
    
    1. Synchronizing on mClosingSyncObject for entire duration of free-form processing, was holding up ImagingThread suspended, when next frame became available and handlePreviewFrame was called. Added additional boolean mbInOCR which indicates a frame is currently being processed.  handlePreviewFrame returns immediately if a frame is being processed.
    2. In case of Multi-Line Form, found an ANR in a situation where Freeform processing thread was busy processing a frame while user already touched the screen to start processing. Since Freeform processing thread and imaging thread are of same priority, freeform processing thread starved imaging thread and this would cause processing timeout and caused an ANR. Added functions in SimulScanPlugin to start/stop processing and also added checks though-out processing code to check for stopped condition. Chose this option instead of killing the freeform thread.
    
    Change-Id: I58d3007b79be135cf282892c79219fcce3bf125b

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Tue Oct 25 15:37:57 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-140134 - Changed SimulScanEngine to look at External storage --> Temporary data (/data/tmp) --> Application data storage in that order while looking for images to read.
    
    Images files are written to $FOLDER/simulscan/log in debug mode. Images are read from $FOLDER/simulscan/image folder. This location is available to end user customer. To avoid scenario where end-user customer inadvertently copies the image files from /log into /image location and the device keeps decoding that, we added a prefix to file name as FileMode_TemplateName_Preview_xxxw_xxxh.yuv and FileMode_TemplateName_Still_xxxw_xxxh.yuv
    
    Added code to decode saved file when generated image format is JPEG.
    
    Change-Id: Id0628b22ef62f4a675da618e36f6a216bc9d0003

commit ada090511c1feede870df35de8d50d9704111070
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 21 13:17:13 2016 -0500

    FileMode Feature: There are two parts to this feature. First phase is image capture in which preview frame used for identification is saved as MainTemplateName_Preview_xxxw_xxxh.yuv and snapshot frame is saved as MainTemplateName_Still_xxxw_xxxh.yuv. For Freeform and Manufacturing there is no snapshot frame. Make sure MainTemplateName does not contain any underscores “-“ and it is one complete word.
    
    In next phase, if files mentioned above exist in the /storage/sdcard0/simulscan/image location and match naming convention and template selected, then that file is used for identification and decoding instead of frames generated by imager or camera.
    
    Change-Id: I64b64343c95dc554f426a4fb00ebb6e06316f56a

commit b06ef68fbbc3355d49ccd2f3eea1ef05274f07e2
Author: Neeta Joshi <hpb743@zebra.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 24 11:44:22 2017 -0500

    According to BSPA-21048 LED implementation in Marshmallow is same as on KK Pollux. This design choice is due to "id" limitations in framework.
    
    To ensure it works as per our need, we need to issue proper sequence of commands. For example we need RED led to glow when scanning starts and
    GREEN when scan is sucessful and LED turns off when app is exits we need to do the following commands
    1) Start of the app -> Notification with RED
    2) Another notification with GREEN -> now RED will glow
    3) On successful scan -> Notification with RED -> now GREEN will glow then go to Step 2
    4) If scan is not successful cancel notification
    5) On existing app show notification with LED off and then one more time show Notification with LED off and then cancel the notification
    
    Change-Id: Ic064bd010697a573d9c28d34702eb838dfa20ec2
    (cherry picked from commit ca413cd386aeccf5ab135544f6dffc5186d4be1d)

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 21 13:17:13 2016 -0500

    FileMode Feature: There are two parts to this feature. First phase is image capture in which preview frame used for identification is saved as MainTemplateName_Preview_xxxw_xxxh.yuv and snapshot frame is saved as MainTemplateName_Still_xxxw_xxxh.yuv. For Freeform and Manufacturing there is no snapshot frame. Make sure MainTemplateName does not contain any underscores “-“ and it is one complete word.
    
    In next phase, if files mentioned above exist in the /storage/sdcard0/simulscan/image location and match naming convention and template selected, then that file is used for identification and decoding instead of frames generated by imager or camera.
    
    Change-Id: I64b64343c95dc554f426a4fb00ebb6e06316f56a

commit f2311d73e52afab40dbc6dcd15941dd470f702c8
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Tue Apr 19 13:02:19 2016 -0500

    MC-125788 - ANR observed while doing suspend resume of the device.
    
    This use-case actually contains SimulScanDemo and Launcher application race condition. When home buttons is HIT, the stop() API call from SimulScanDemo application does not complete since ImagingThread is busy processing data. In the meantime Launcher starts and tries to apply a template and open the camera.
    
    Set the state to DecodingState.STOPPED_SESSION first, before continuing to stop in the decoding engine, so that all callbacks and post processing stops too.
    
    Change-Id: I7cd34fd87ed0cedb4f9490ed0e3d7f5c4b1f1882

commit 60a22cd127b3e92f2a62561397d4bf118895e60f
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 7 11:55:51 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-124327 ANR observed on Multi line template - Category: Flash On/Off Stress
    
    Fix MC-124584 ANR was observed & application did not launch View finder while capturing Unstructured templates
    
    1. Synchronizing on mClosingSyncObject for entire duration of free-form processing, was holding up ImagingThread suspended, when next frame became available and handlePreviewFrame was called. Added additional boolean mbInOCR which indicates a frame is currently being processed.  handlePreviewFrame returns immediately if a frame is being processed.
    2. In case of Multi-Line Form, found an ANR in a situation where Freeform processing thread was busy processing a frame while user already touched the screen to start processing. Since Freeform processing thread and imaging thread are of same priority, freeform processing thread starved imaging thread and this would cause processing timeout and caused an ANR. Added functions in SimulScanPlugin to start/stop processing and also added checks though-out processing code to check for stopped condition. Chose this option instead of killing the freeform thread.
    
    Change-Id: I58d3007b79be135cf282892c79219fcce3bf125b

    MC-125788 - ANR observed while doing suspend resume of the device.
    
    This use-case actually contains SimulScanDemo and Launcher application race condition. When home buttons is HIT, the stop() API call from SimulScanDemo application does not complete since ImagingThread is busy processing data. In the meantime Launcher starts and tries to apply a template and open the camera.
    
    Set the state to DecodingState.STOPPED_SESSION first, before continuing to stop in the decoding engine, so that all callbacks and post processing stops too.

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 7 11:55:51 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-124327 ANR observed on Multi line template - Category: Flash On/Off Stress
    
    Fix MC-124584 ANR was observed & application did not launch View finder while capturing Unstructured templates
    
    1. Synchronizing on mClosingSyncObject for entire duration of free-form processing, was holding up ImagingThread suspended, when next frame became available and handlePreviewFrame was called. Added additional boolean mbInOCR which indicates a frame is currently being processed.  handlePreviewFrame returns immediately if a frame is being processed.
    2. In case of Multi-Line Form, found an ANR in a situation where Freeform processing thread was busy processing a frame while user already touched the screen to start processing. Since Freeform processing thread and imaging thread are of same priority, freeform processing thread starved imaging thread and this would cause processing timeout and caused an ANR. Added functions in SimulScanPlugin to start/stop processing and also added checks though-out processing code to check for stopped condition. Chose this option instead of killing the freeform thread.
    
    Change-Id: I58d3007b79be135cf282892c79219fcce3bf125b

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 21 13:17:13 2016 -0500

    FileMode Feature: There are two parts to this feature. First phase is image capture in which preview frame used for identification is saved as MainTemplateName_Preview_xxxw_xxxh.yuv and snapshot frame is saved as MainTemplateName_Still_xxxw_xxxh.yuv. For Freeform and Manufacturing there is no snapshot frame. Make sure MainTemplateName does not contain any underscores “-“ and it is one complete word.
    
    In next phase, if files mentioned above exist in the /storage/sdcard0/simulscan/image location and match naming convention and template selected, then that file is used for identification and decoding instead of frames generated by imager or camera.
    
    Change-Id: I64b64343c95dc554f426a4fb00ebb6e06316f56a

commit b06ef68fbbc3355d49ccd2f3eea1ef05274f07e2
Author: Neeta Joshi <hpb743@zebra.com>
Date:   Mon Apr 24 11:44:22 2017 -0500

    According to BSPA-21048 LED implementation in Marshmallow is same as on KK Pollux. This design choice is due to "id" limitations in framework.
    
    To ensure it works as per our need, we need to issue proper sequence of commands. For example we need RED led to glow when scanning starts and
    GREEN when scan is sucessful and LED turns off when app is exits we need to do the following commands
    1) Start of the app -> Notification with RED
    2) Another notification with GREEN -> now RED will glow
    3) On successful scan -> Notification with RED -> now GREEN will glow then go to Step 2
    4) If scan is not successful cancel notification
    5) On existing app show notification with LED off and then one more time show Notification with LED off and then cancel the notification
    
    Change-Id: Ic064bd010697a573d9c28d34702eb838dfa20ec2
    (cherry picked from commit ca413cd386aeccf5ab135544f6dffc5186d4be1d)

    To ensure it works as per our need, we need to issue proper sequence of commands. For example we need RED led to glow when scanning starts and
    GREEN when scan is sucessful and LED turns off when app is exits we need to do the following commands
    1) Start of the app -> Notification with RED
    2) Another notification with GREEN -> now RED will glow
    3) On successful scan -> Notification with RED -> now GREEN will glow then go to Step 2
    4) If scan is not successful cancel notification
    5) On existing app show notification with LED off and then one more time show Notification with LED off and then cancel the notification

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 8 13:10:04 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-119528 - Launcher issue observed when the Simulscan plug-in is enabled from data wedge and scanning the postal document
    
    mViewfinderDialog.setOnKeyListener(null), when we cancel UI Dialog, otherwise we receive onKey callback even after UI Dialog is removed. This was causing screen lockup.
    
    The ANR is caused by the UI thread being locked up. In SimulScanEngine, we are blocking the main thread (thread used to call into SimulScan.start()) while waiting for the UI thread to create and display the viewfinder dialog. But, the dialog creation code never runs. We cannot find in our code why the UI thread blocks. So as not to cause an ANR, we added a timeout in start() and throw SIMULSCAN_SW_ERROR exception, if UI Thread is blocked for more than 4 seconds.
    
    Change-Id: I524114441ffeb0b991f7a9c81a9a0b909718ec45

    Corrective Actions:

Since there is no call order requirement, checking for validity in either calls is not feasible. Date:   Fri Mar 25 08:54:48 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-111477 - Flash option is not available for the default templates & for manually created templates flash goes off after multiple scans using any templates which uses camera scanner
    
    Template builder, puts <dparam id="flash_mode" type="integer" value="1" /> which user chooses to turn on flash and nothing in the template when user wants it off. On the device if previously loaded template disabled flash and next template does not explicitly turn on flash , then the flash option did not get enabled even if was camera.
    Corrective Action:
    As a solution, on camera, flash is never disabled. If flash is disabled in camera mode (due to previous session/template), we keep flash turned off, but the icon in available on the Viewfinder for user to turn it on if he wants.
    
    Change-Id: I7a2609a8bdb68c9e9b69bab79a28e16c579a5156

Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 21 13:17:13 2016 -0500

    FileMode Feature: There are two parts to this feature. First phase is image capture in which preview frame used for identification is saved as MainTemplateName_Preview_xxxw_xxxh.yuv and snapshot frame is saved as MainTemplateName_Still_xxxw_xxxh.yuv. For Freeform and Manufacturing there is no snapshot frame. Make sure MainTemplateName does not contain any underscores “-“ and it is one complete word.
    
    In next phase, if files mentioned above exist in the /storage/sdcard0/simulscan/image location and match naming convention and template selected, then that file is used for identification and decoding instead of frames generated by imager or camera.
    
    Change-Id: I64b64343c95dc554f426a4fb00ebb6e06316f56a

commit 5acea748c25c681b36495141e36ecbcbf6d0e32d
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Tue May 24 08:30:01 2016 -0500

    Fix SS - 171 - Imager: Simulscan engine gets stuck at 'capturing remain still' and results in processing timeout
    
    When imager is selected as input source, auto capture feature has no relevance. SimulScanEngine was processing hard-trigger and touch even when imager was chosen as the input source.
    
    Added code to ignore hard-trigger when imager is the chosen source.
    
    Change-Id: Ia1c3a99dbe01654fae122db7dd26b3cd75a8f863

commit 7a8411f339b94434f9e3c33787c358f75a16358a
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Thu May 19 13:01:07 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-126657 - ANR is seen in TC55 stress test
    
    This test called start-stop using a program. When Processing Timeout occurred AlertDialog would pop-up on the screen. The program could start next session of scanning without dismissing the AlertDialog. This would cause multiple AlertDialog to be created and eventually caused ANR.
    Added checks and methods to Dismiss AlertDialogs that are previously created, inside appropriate functions.
    
    Change-Id: I96466dd296481e1f8cff0d071cda131a523a51f7

commit 0379e7c15b941af9a7ae219317b41f3b1a1177c4
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 8 13:10:04 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-119528 - Launcher issue observed when the Simulscan plug-in is enabled from data wedge and scanning the postal document
    
    mViewfinderDialog.setOnKeyListener(null), when we cancel UI Dialog, otherwise we receive onKey callback even after UI Dialog is removed. This was causing screen lockup.
    
    The ANR is caused by the UI thread being locked up. In SimulScanEngine, we are blocking the main thread (thread used to call into SimulScan.start()) while waiting for the UI thread to create and display the viewfinder dialog. But, the dialog creation code never runs. We cannot find in our code why the UI thread blocks. So as not to cause an ANR, we added a timeout in start() and throw SIMULSCAN_SW_ERROR exception, if UI Thread is blocked for more than 4 seconds.
    
    Change-Id: I524114441ffeb0b991f7a9c81a9a0b909718ec45

commit 1f4e24578d1e3b5e81bac8c415beb9733466c0c9
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Mon Mar 14 15:29:30 2016 -0500

    Add a NULL check for mSimulScanView. onKey can be called from android, even after view is hidden. It can be kept alive since GC has not yet collected it yet.
    
    Need to return true only if we consume the key press, otherwise return false for other views to consume.
    Change-Id: I2a9785071f260317ea85f235cfe7dfe34fd9ee0d

    SimulScan Document Capture V1.12.9
    
    Changes to accommodate for New Scanning Framework changes. New scanning framework returns frame data on a different thread than the one on which open/close are called. This caused synchronization issues on SimulScan. Changed SimulScan code to post the frame handling to ImagingThread, if callback is called on different thread.

    Fix MC-129415 - [TC75-L]  Observed continues image capture sound while capturing the postal image  and process ends with "processing time out" message.
    
    BSP has introduced new system variable “persist.sys.stopshuttersound” which can be set to ‘1’ to disable shutter sound and ‘0’ to enable shutter sound back.
    
    Made changes to SimulScanEngine to integrate BSP changes.

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder

    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)

children.name: Default - Unstructured Multi-Line.xml
children.commit_data:
commit 3cb2f47278bd4c3a5491cff2fcb926bc3d2ed3b0
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@zebra.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 21 18:26:13 2014 -0500

    SimulScanEngine: Modify freeform OCR so that only one processing mode is used
    
    -In <region> tag, an attribute called “view” is added; the value is set to the view the viewfinder should start with when it sees this region
    -In <procmode> tag, keep “ptype” attribute as “ocr” for all OCR, regardless of what type (region, single, multi)
    -In an <rparam>, a parameter called “type” to indicate the type of OCR processing we will be doing (cropped_region, single, multi) is added. For backward compatibility, if this parameter is not specified, we will default to “cropped_region” (which is the legacy OCR processing mode).
    -The <sstemplate> “ttype” attribute drives how the XML is interpreted. For example, if we are in a “mixed” ttype, we will not accept OCR types of “single” and “multi”, and we will require x, y, width, and height. (Not implemented as of now)

commit cf8c27a28b57dd66fed45d8a09087e9ac8f3268e

Date:   Thu Nov 6 19:24:22 2014 -0500

commit e4b13da963d3151ebc49b6d2e86e308a762e4c76
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 2 15:35:45 2014 -0400

    Implemented single line and multi-line freeform OCR
    
    -ImgProc V2.8.5
    -Split out structured use-case elements to separate XML file
            -Begin creating placeholder XML files for other use-cases
    -Subclassed OCRPlugin for freeform OCR
    -Code cleanup
            -Simplify camera initialization code in SimulScanEngineConcrete.java
            -Moved YUV stride method into SimulScanUtils.java
            -copyDefaultTemplates(...) moved into FileIO.java
            -Move ImgKit parameter setting code to ImgKit.java
            -Moved auto resolution algorithm to ColorCamera.java
            -Created Builder class for ProcessedRegion
    -Implemented passing rotation information to freeform OCR plugins
    -Implemented coordinate system to map between screen resolution and image resolution using ScalableRectangle class
    -Created unstructured single line and multi-line default templates

commit 35926ca274618f6fb062ef27349b2b4ee837bb8c
Author: Neeta <Neeta.Joshi@zebra.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 7 12:07:00 2016 -0500

    Fix MC-129423 - Unable to save manually modified data after scan capture in samulscan for "Structured_European.xml" Template.
    
    The reason for this issue is that, the CANCEL and OK buttons were pushed out of screen view. The buttons were pushed out since the image rendered in the ImageView had white space on top and bottom when Android scales an image which is bigger than the ImageView; due to resizing . Added two fold fix for this:
    
    1. adjustViewBounds=true is set to make ImageView resize itself to fit the rescaled image.
    2. Footer, which contains CANCEL and OK buttons, is defined first in the xml, so that even if scrollview occupies full screen, CANCEL and OK buttons are still visible.
    
    Change-Id: Iddc0dad4c4f928bdada53c4095115675732348ce

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

Date:   Tue Sep 30 12:13:23 2014 -0400

    Template update: Update <ssmain> "version" attribute to "2.0"
    
    -Major versions are not compatible with each other (e.g. 1.0 and 2.0)
    -Minor versions will be backward compatible with each other (e.g. 1.0 and 1.1)
    -Check is done in MainTemplate to enforce these rules

commit e1d23b4ac3e89994ad8bb1349c5d9c8ae8128368
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 23 16:51:08 2014 -0400

    Image Kit update (v6.1)
    
    1.Enabled to generate bounding box for MicroPDF, Maxicode, Aztec. Combined with QR, MiroQR, DataMatrix, PDF which are already supported, the current ImageKit is able to generate bounding box for all 2D barcodes except Han Xin.
    
    Image Kit update (v6.0)
    
    1. New architecture to handle high-res 2D barcodes in SimulScan.
       Please refer to doc"SimulScan_2D_Barcode.doc" on compass: http://compass.mot-solutions.com/doc/485034614/SimulScan_2D_barcode.doc
    2. Change Macro N_THRESH_NEIGHBORS in MATCODES.C to 9 to improve QR decoding performance
    3. Default length of a decodable Korean 3Of5 string is changed to 6.
    
    DCS clearcase label: IMGKIT_6.01D13_DPX08
    libADCOcr.a: version 1.4.8
    
    SimulScanEngine: Architectural changes to support new Image Kit
    
    -Identification and processing is now in one session
    -Changed method names for testing frames on Image Kit
    -Fixed timing issue for Image Kit where token reset was being sent in the middle of addFrame(...)
    -Fixed library, threading for deinitializing UI
    -Updated templates

commit 6a2c7980bbe554885ca10599ae6053e04f297c87
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 24 14:16:26 2014 -0400

    SimulScanEngine: Add back in logic to copy default templates to default TEMPLATE_DIR
    
    -Change ssparams.xml TEMPLATE_DIR default value to point to /enterprise/device/settings/datawedge/templates
    -Default templates are prefixed with "Default - "
    -Parameter file moved locally to TEMPLATE_DIR and only is responsible for tracking changes to the engine version for the templates

children.name: Default - Unstructured Multi-Line.xml
children.commit_data:
commit 3cb2f47278bd4c3a5491cff2fcb926bc3d2ed3b0
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@zebra.com>
Date:   Fri Nov 21 18:26:13 2014 -0500

    SimulScanEngine: Modify freeform OCR so that only one processing mode is used
    
    -In <region> tag, an attribute called “view” is added; the value is set to the view the viewfinder should start with when it sees this region
    -In <procmode> tag, keep “ptype” attribute as “ocr” for all OCR, regardless of what type (region, single, multi)
    -In an <rparam>, a parameter called “type” to indicate the type of OCR processing we will be doing (cropped_region, single, multi) is added. For backward compatibility, if this parameter is not specified, we will default to “cropped_region” (which is the legacy OCR processing mode).
    -The <sstemplate> “ttype” attribute drives how the XML is interpreted. For example, if we are in a “mixed” ttype, we will not accept OCR types of “single” and “multi”, and we will require x, y, width, and height. (Not implemented as of now)

commit e4b13da963d3151ebc49b6d2e86e308a762e4c76
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu Oct 2 15:35:45 2014 -0400

    Implemented single line and multi-line freeform OCR
    
    -ImgProc V2.8.5
    -Split out structured use-case elements to separate XML file
            -Begin creating placeholder XML files for other use-cases
    -Subclassed OCRPlugin for freeform OCR
    -Code cleanup
            -Simplify camera initialization code in SimulScanEngineConcrete.java
            -Moved YUV stride method into SimulScanUtils.java
            -copyDefaultTemplates(...) moved into FileIO.java
            -Move ImgKit parameter setting code to ImgKit.java
            -Moved auto resolution algorithm to ColorCamera.java
            -Created Builder class for ProcessedRegion
    -Implemented passing rotation information to freeform OCR plugins
    -Implemented coordinate system to map between screen resolution and image resolution using ScalableRectangle class
    -Created unstructured single line and multi-line default templates

Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>

    Image Kit update (v6.1)
    
    1.Enabled to generate bounding box for MicroPDF, Maxicode, Aztec. Combined with QR, MiroQR, DataMatrix, PDF which are already supported, the current ImageKit is able to generate bounding box for all 2D barcodes except Han Xin.
    
    Image Kit update (v6.0)
    
    1. New architecture to handle high-res 2D barcodes in SimulScan.
       Please refer to doc"SimulScan_2D_Barcode.doc" on compass: http://compass.mot-solutions.com/doc/485034614/SimulScan_2D_barcode.doc
    2. Change Macro N_THRESH_NEIGHBORS in MATCODES.C to 9 to improve QR decoding performance

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

commit bf361a63e38e996522c8efd8d6afa8bd86b2c899
Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>
Date:   Thu May 29 15:10:57 2014 -0400

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder
    -Added gradle wrapper to allow building of project for users without Gradle
    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

Author: Lawrence Ng <lawrence.ng@motorolasolutions.com>

    Include automated building of device releases using Gradle
    
    -Updated .gitignore to ignore files in folder called ".gradle" and "bin"
    -Moved Engineering Application Readme.txt content to new file under Docs folder
    -Updated Readme.txt to describe directory structure of repository
    -Include Framework build files under Framework folder

    -Included Tools/signapk.jar to allow for signing of apk files
    -Removed reference to INPUT_SOURCE_FILE in SimulScanDemo code
    -Remove built APKs from build tree, since we have standalone build capability
    
    Build script does the following:
    -Create "bin" directory with "Release" and "Engineering" subdirectories
    -Create product directories (currently MC67 and TC55) inside "Release" folder
    -Copy framework files properly into product directory folders
    -Build and sign SimulScanRes project
    -Modify SimulScanR.java using resource values obtained from SimulScanRes build
    -Build SimulScanEngine project using Proguard for release build to remove verbose and debug log messages
    -Utilize SDK Add-On to build and sign SimulScanDemo framework project (modifying AndroidManifest.xml accordingly)
    -Create UpdatePackage zip file
    -Create standalone APKs alongside framework APKs
    -Write version numbers to Android applications based on build script
    -Build release SimulScanRes with some parameters removed (engineering SimulScanRes APK still has all parameters)
    -Build different product flavors for SimulScanEngine to enable/disable logs; build different standalone APKs accordingly
    -Copy prebuilt SDK Add-On into "Release" folder and SDK Add-On build files into "Engineering" folder
    
    Current Issues
    -Buildscript may not be doing things optimally and "correctly" from a build script philosophical standpoint
    -NDK code is not built in script (only copied over from "libs" folder)

    Added scripts to build partial update packages. These are just copy, zip and sign scripts. These scripts piggy-back on the fact that build.gradle has been run and all the required binaries are already generated. The order of commands is as below:
    
    gradle clean
    gradle compile
    gradle -b simulscandemoapp.gradle buildsimulscandemo
    gradle -b engine.gradle buildengine
    gradle -b imgkit.gradle buildimgkit
    gradle -b imgproc.gradle buildimgproc
